Note:
By default hands are NOT hidden. If you need to hide hands (e.g. Sealed Orders mission) click "Options > Hands > Hiding: Default"

For instructions on how to make your own map, click the Notebook in the top toolbar.

Objective markers have a 3" circle state so you can easily check range and a generic back for hidden objectives.
 
The Tactical Objective Decks should snap onto the "Objective Deck" and "Discard" slots.

Credits can be found in the Notepad.

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
-- Map Extractor
convertBtn={
    label="Convert", click_function="convert", function_owner=self,
    position={0,1,0}, rotation={0,270,0}, height=1200, width=3500, scale={2,2,2},
    font_size=700, color={0.5,0.5,0.5}, font_color={1,1,1}
}
urlDisplay={
    label="The url of the old mat", input_function="none", function_owner=self,
    alignment=3, position={0,1,0}, rotation={0,270,0}, height=500, width=400,
    font_size=400, tooltip="",
    value=""
}
imageUrl=""
playZone=nil
playZoneData={
    type = "ScriptingTrigger",
    position          = {x=-18, y=20, z=0.2},
    rotation          = {x=0, y=0, z=0},
    scale             = {x=72.2, y=40, z=48.4},
    sound             = false,
    snap_to_grid      = false,
}

flexTableGuid="bd69bd"

function onSave()
    saved_data = JSON.encode({svimageUrl=imageUrl})
    --saved_data = ""
    return saved_data
end

function onLoad(saved_data)
    if saved_data ~= "" then
         local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
         imageUrl = loaded_data.svimageUrl
    else
        imageUrl = ""
    end
    if imageUrl == "" then
        self.createButton(convertBtn)
    else
        urlDisplay.width=string.len(imageUrl)*200
        urlDisplay.value=imageUrl
        self.createInput(urlDisplay)
    end


end

function convert()
    local obj_surface = getObjectFromGUID("4ee1f2")
    local customInfo = obj_surface.getCustomObject()
    imageUrl= customInfo.diffuse
    print (imageUrl)
    urlDisplay.width=string.len(imageUrl)*200
    urlDisplay.value=imageUrl
    self.createInput(urlDisplay)
    self.clearButtons()
    --print("Converting...")
    spawnPlayZone()
    Wait.frames(convert2, 3)
end

function convert2()
    --print("Starting to delete")
    deleteTable()
    local allObj=getAllObjects()
    local zoneObj=playZone.getObjects()
    for i, objA in ipairs(allObj) do
        local delete=true
        for j, objZ in ipairs (zoneObj) do
            if objA == objZ or objA == self then
                delete=false
                objZ.setLock(true)

            end
        end
        if delete then
            objA.destroy()
        end
    end
    moveAll()
    self.setPosition({-42,2,0})
    --self.destroy()
end

function deleteTable()
    --flexTable=getObjectFromGUID(flexTableGuid)
    local guidList = {
        "afc863","c8edca","393bf7","12c65e","f938a2","9f95fd","35b95f",
        "5af8f2","4ee1f2","bd69bd"
    }
    for i, tbl in ipairs(guidList) do
        getObjectFromGUID(tbl).destroy()
    end
end

function moveAll()
    local toMove=getAllObjects()
    for i, obj in ipairs(toMove) do
        local newPos={}
        newPos={obj.getPosition().x+18,obj.getPosition().y-0.52,obj.getPosition().z}
        obj.setPosition(newPos)
    end
end

function spawnPlayZone()
    playZone=spawnObject(playZoneData)
end

function none()
end

0.title: Instructions
0.body:
Click the white button on the lower left corner of the table (to the bottom and right of the blue players dice roller), copy the template URL and open in a browser to save it.

Edit the maps background using GIMP or whatever. The black part is the 6'x4' playing area.

Make a custom tile, and put your map onto it to upload it to the Steam Cloud. Copy this URL.

Click the white button on the lower left corner of the table, replace the template URL with the Steam Cloud URL of your map. Click "Apply Image to Table Surface". Save the game then reload.

Set up terrain as desired etc.

Save game, Load Game, Upload to workshop as usual if so desired.

How to import a table image: https://youtu.be/xKzAf-fu1KQ
